{{Quote|A lot of people say they wanna save the world, but Hope, she saves it every day.|[[Scott Lang]]|Ant-Man and the Wasp: Quantumania}}
'''Hope van Dyne''' is the daughter of [[Hank Pym]] and [[Janet van Dyne]] and a former chairwoman of the board of [[Pym Technologies]]. When [[Darren Cross]] attempted to create and sell a new [[Yellowjacket Suit|weapon]] based on her father's [[Ant-Man Suit]], van Dyne reunited with her father and, along with [[Scott Lang]], who succeeded Hank as Ant-Man, was able to defeat Cross. Following these events, Pym realized there was a possibility of saving his wife due to Lang's first experience in the [[Quantum Realm]]. This resulted in van Dyne  finally being offered a [[Wasp Suit|suit]] that belonged to her mother by her father, therefore taking on the name of '''Wasp'''.

Over the course of [[2016|another year]], van Dyne would train alongside Lang, while forming a romantic relationship with him, until she broke up with him because Lang's actions during the [[Battle at Leipzig-Halle Airport]] resulted in her and her father being wanted by the [[FBI]]. [[2018|Two years later]], van Dyne, Pym, and Lang successfully managed to [[Rescue of Janet van Dyne|retrieve]] her mother from the Quantum Realm and also faced [[Ava Starr]] when she became a threat to their plan of rescue. Van Dyne also reconciled with Lang and resumed their relationship.

Alongside her parents, van Dyne was among the half the population who turned to dust following [[Thanos]]' [[Snap]]. [[2023|Five years later]], during the [[Battle of Earth]], van Dyne was [[Blip|resurrected]], and she aided the [[Avengers]] in defeating [[Thanos/Cosmic Time Heist|Thanos]] and his army. After Thanos' army was disintegrated, van Dyne attended [[Tony Stark]]'s funeral with Lang and her parents and later returned home to [[San Francisco]] to celebrate their victory with [[Cassie Lang]].

In [[2026]], Hope and the rest of her family were sucked into the Quantum Realm through a [[Quantum Satellite]] created by Cassie. Separated from Scott, Hope followed Janet as she reunited with [[Krylar]], only to be betrayed by him, forcing them to escape. She would later reunite with Scott and help him retrieve the [[Multiversal Engine Core]] at the behest of [[Kang the Conqueror]]. Hope, alongside her family, confronted and defeated Kang during the [[Uprising in Axia]], killing him and safely returning to the surface world.

==Biography==
{{MD|Hope Van Dyne (Earth-199999)}}
===Early Life===
====Daughter of Heroes====
[[File:Pym van Dyne.png|{{AltFloat}}|Hope van Dyne as a baby with her parents]]
{{Quote|Mommy?"<br>"Oh, Jellybean. [[Hank Pym|Daddy]] and I have a last minute business trip, so [[Rose (Nanny)|Rose]] is going to stay with you for a few days."<br>"No. I don't want you to go.|Hope van Dyne and [[Janet van Dyne]]|Ant-Man and the Wasp}}
Hope van Dyne was born to scientists [[Hank Pym]] and [[Janet van Dyne]], who were also [[S.H.I.E.L.D.]] operatives codenamed Ant-Man and Wasp, respectively. Hope was more connected to her mother and loved playing games with her, especially hide and seek, in which Hope always hid in the wardrobe. Whenever Pym and Janet had to go on missions, they would leave Hope at home with her nanny, [[Rose (Nanny)|Rose]], while they were gone, telling their daughter they were going on business trips.{{Ref|AMatW}}

====Losing Her Mother====
[[File:Hope young 4.png|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne watches her parents leave]]
{{Quote|You know when my [[Janet van Dyne|mother]] died, I didn't see [[Hank Pym|him]] for two weeks?"<br>"He was in grief."<br>"Yeah, so was I, and I was seven. And he never came back, not in any way that counted. He just sent me off to boarding school.|Hope van Dyne and [[Scott Lang]]|Ant-Man (film)}}
One night, van Dyne was awakened by her parents, who were speaking with [[Rose (Nanny)|Rose]]. Van Dyne called out to her [[Janet van Dyne|mother]], who informed van Dyne that she and her [[Hank Pym|father]] were going on a business trip. However, van Dyne didn't want them to go, so Janet put her daughter at ease by saying that it was going to be boring, making her laugh by jokingly falling asleep. After her father said his goodbyes, van Dyne watched as her parents left the house.
[[File:Hope learns her mother died.png|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne learns about her [[Janet van Dyne|mother]]'s death]]
Later, van Dyne was reunited with her father, who returned home, but sadly not her mother, which Pym had to explain that she was never coming back, telling his daughter that her mother had died.{{Ref|AMatW}} For the next two weeks, van Dyne would not see her father, as the substantial grief caused him to become lost and neglect her, not giving van Dyne the needed support. When Pym returned, he decided to send van Dyne away to boarding school.{{Ref|AM}}

===Working at Pym Tech===
====Voting Out Hank Pym====
{{Quote|I wouldn't help [[Yellowjacket|him]] so he conspired against me and he voted me out of my [[Pym Technologies|own company]]."<br>"How could he do that?"<br>"The board's chairman is my daughter, Hope. She was the deciding vote.|[[Hank Pym]] and [[Scott Lang]]|Ant-Man (film)}}
In adulthood, van Dyne worked her way up to becoming chairperson of the board of directors at [[Pym Technologies]], where she cast the deciding vote that ousted [[Hank Pym]] from the company. She then proceeded to work at [[Cross Technologies]] as [[Darren Cross]]' assistant. However, van Dyne discovered he was attempting to replicate her father's designs for the [[Ant-Man Suit]], intending to sell it to [[Hydra]]. Fearing the consequences, van Dyne contacted her father and convinced him to assist her in stopping Cross.{{Ref|AM}}

====Darren Cross' Presentation====
[[File:Hope van Dyne (2015).jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne at the [[Yellowjacket Suit|Yellowjacket]] presentation]]
{{Quote|Good morning, Hank."<br>"Hope. Would it kill you to call me 'Dad?'"<br>"Well, [[Darren Cross|Dr. Cross]] will be so pleased that you could find the time to join [[Cross Technologies|us]] today.|Hope van Dyne and [[Hank Pym]]|Ant-Man (film)}}
When [[Darren Cross]] organized a presentation of his [[Yellowjacket Suit]] to potential investors, van Dyne attended and greeted [[Hank Pym]] when he arrived, although she refused to call him "Dad" and instead referred to him as "Doctor Pym." Van Dyne stayed close as Cross presented the armor and its abilities. Once it was over, she spoke to Pym about their plan to stop Cross, and Pym revealed that he had found a [[Scott Lang|person]] who could assist them in their mission. Van Dyne attempted to push for Pym to allow her to complete the mission herself but he refused to allow her to take the same risks that her mother had taken.{{Ref|AM}}

====Dinner with Darren Cross====
[[File:Hope-Dinner.jpeg|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne has dinner with [[Darren Cross]]]]
{{Quote|[[Hank Pym|His]] failures as a mentor, as a father, forced us to spread our wings."<br>"You're a success, Darren. You deserve everything coming your way.|[[Darren Cross]] and Hope van Dyne|Ant-Man (film)}}
To celebrate his success, [[Darren Cross]] invited van Dyne to dinner at a restaurant. There, Cross began to rant about both of their fractured relationships with [[Hank Pym]] before van Dyne toasted to Cross' accomplishments, preaching that Cross deserved everything that was coming to him.{{Ref|AM}}

====Recreating Pym Particles====
[[File:Hope-Particle-testing.jpeg|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne expresses her concerns to Cross]]
{{Quote|I thought we were using mice?"<br>"What's the difference? Commence experiment 34C, organic atomic reduction."<br>"Darren, maybe we should think...|Hope van Dyne and [[Darren Cross]]|Ant-Man (film)}}
Back at [[Pym Technologies]], van Dyne and [[Darren Cross]] continued their work to complete their version of the [[Pym Particles]]. Cross, instead of using mice as originally believed, began using lambs in his experiments. However, the tests continued to prove unsuccessful and the lambs were crushed under the pressure of shrinking in size; these failures did not stop Cross and he continued to bring out new subjects, much to van Dyne's ever-growing concern.{{Ref|AM}}

===Meeting Scott Lang===
====Little Faith====
[[File:HopePym.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne watches over [[Scott Lang]]]]
{{Quote|Have you been standing there watching me sleep this whole time?"<br>"Yes."<br>"Why?"<br>"Because the last time you were here, you stole [[Ant-Man Suit|something]].|[[Scott Lang]] and Hope van Dyne|Ant-Man (film)}}
[[Hank Pym]] chose [[Scott Lang]] to assist them in their mission; however, van Dyne remained skeptical of whether or not they really needed outside help. In order to assess Lang, Pym set out a test in which he would give Lang the information needed to break into his home and steal the [[Ant-Man Suit]]. Lang completed the task with ease, despite not knowing he was being tested and went on to accidentally test out the suit, causing him to shrink to the size of an ant. The experience horrified Lang and he attempted to return the suit, but van Dyne used the opportunity to call [[San Francisco Police Department]] and have him arrested as he attempted to leave [[Pym Residence]].
[[File:HopeVanDyne-Questions-Lang.jpeg|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne remains skeptical about Lang]]
Pym broke Lang out of prison and brought him back to his mansion; van Dyne kept watch over Lang as he slept, having passed out while riding an ant. When Lang awoke, he questioned why van Dyne was watching him and she explained it was because last time he was there, he had stolen something. She took Lang downstairs to be introduced to Pym. They explained their mission to him, although van Dyne continued to recommend that they not use Lang and instead allow her to break into [[Pym Technologies]] and steal the [[Yellowjacket Suit]] from Cross herself, but Pym continued to refuse. He explained the details of the plan and why Lang was selected and eventually, the latter agreed to help them.{{Ref|AM}}

====Training Scott Lang====
[[File:Ant-Man screenshot 38.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne trains Lang in martial arts]]
{{Quote|You're going to have to learn how to punch."<br>"You're going to show me how to punch? Show me how to punch."<br>"That's how you punch.|Hope van Dyne and [[Scott Lang]]|Ant-Man (film)}}
Van Dyne had been tasked with training [[Scott Lang]] on how to fight with the [[Ant-Man Suit]] to cause the most effective but non-lethal damage. Lang initially scoffed at the idea as he claimed that his three years in prison had taught him how to fight and to prove this he punched van Dyne but she easily blocked the attack and called him out for the poor attempt. Lang challenged her to show him how to punch, which she did by easily punching him in the face despite his attempts to block. Lang accepted van Dyne's help after this and together, they trained hard, fighting each other without holding back until van Dyne was satisfied with his abilities.
[[File:Hank-Pym-Hope-Train-Scott.png|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne and [[Hank Pym]] train Lang]]
In a key stage of the training, [[Hank Pym]] taught Lang how to master using the [[Ant-Man Suit]] by jumping through a small key-hole and emerging large on the other side. Van Dyne stood with Pym as Lang failed time after time until he finally mastered the skill. She later joined her father outside as he introduced Lang to the many breeds of [[Ants]] which would be assisting him in his mission. They became amused as Lang would often panic at the size and scale of the ants and regrow to his original size while inside the tunnels.
[[File:HopeVanDyne-Father-Argument.jpeg|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne is insulted by Pym's outburst]]
One skill Lang still struggled to master was communicating with the ants to get them to do his bidding. This continued until van Dyne became frustrated and stepped in, demonstrating her own skills with the communication, telling Pym that she should be the one going on the mission in Lang's place; however, she appeared to almost losing control of the ants, summoning far more than required to complete the simple task of placing a cube of sugar in a cup of tea, until her father intervened to refocus her attention.
[[File:Hope-Lang-Car-Scene.jpeg|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne helps Lang master his skills]]
Utterly frustrated with how her father had continued to underestimate her, van Dyne angrily left the mansion and sat in her car. Lang joined her and tried to comfort her and van Dyne explained to him how Pym had been holding her back ever since her [[Janet van Dyne|mother]]'s death. They discussed Lang's daughter, [[Cassie Lang]], and how he was doing the mission for her. Van Dyne softened and taught Lang a new technique for communicating with the ants, allowing him to make them pick up and spin a coin.{{Ref|AM}}

====Learning the Truth====
[[File:Ant-Man (film) 10.png|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne learns of her mother's sacrifice]]
{{Quote|It's not your fault. [[Janet van Dyne|She]] made her choice. But why didn't you tell me this sooner?"<br>"I was trying to protect you. I lost your mother. I didn't mean to lose you, too.|Hope van Dyne and [[Hank Pym]]|Ant-Man (film)}}
Returning to the house, they found [[Hank Pym]] in the [[Pym Residence]]'s main room. He finally relented and told van Dyne about the day that [[Janet van Dyne]] had died, explaining that in the [[1980s]], they worked as a superhero team with her taking the mantle of Wasp. Pym told her how they had been sent on a mission to intercept a missile which was going to destroy a major city and Janet had sacrificed herself by shrinking into the missile. However, she became lost within the [[Quantum Realm]], which Pym had spent the next few decades trying to understand. Van Dyne hugged her father, with the two finally rebuilding their relationship, although the moment was somewhat ruined by Lang's comments.{{Ref|AM}}

====[[Duel at the Avengers Compound|Duel at the Avengers Facility]]====
[[File:HopeVanDyne-Falcon-Fight.jpeg|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne watches [[Ant-Man]] duel the [[Sam Wilson|Falcon]]]]
{{Quote|Hi, I'm Scott."<br>"Did he just say "Hi, I'm Scott"?|[[Scott Lang]] and Hope van Dyne|Ant-Man (film)}}
In order to test [[Scott Lang]]'s new abilities with the [[Ant-Man Suit]], van Dyne and [[Hank Pym]] sent Lang on a mission to one of [[Howard Stark]]'s old facilities to locate a small device for their heist. Lang quickly realized that the base was now the [[Avengers Compound]] and van Dyne ordered him to abort the mission. Lang chose instead to continue and was confronted by [[Sam Wilson|Falcon]], who tried to force Lang to leave when he introduced himself, leaving van Dyne horrified at the blunder. The two engaged in a brief fight which ended with Lang managing to damage [[EXO-7 Falcon]] and escape, impressing van Dyne somewhat by displaying martial arts moves she had taught him during his brief training during the skirmish.{{Ref|AM}}

====Darren Cross Visits====
[[File:HopeVanDyne-HesGoingToKillHim.jpeg|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne hears [[Darren Cross]] arrive]]
{{Quote|I just saw [[Hank Pym|Hank]]. I still get nothing but contempt from him."<br>"Don't let him rile you up, he's just... He's just a senile old man.|[[Darren Cross]] and Hope van Dyne|Ant-Man (film)}}
While the team rested from the mission (for which van Dyne congratulated Lang for), Pym stepped into the next room only to be greeted by Cross, who had broken into the mansion. Cross claimed he had come in simply because the door was open and calmly spoke to Pym. Van Dyne and Lang realized in a panic that Cross could easily see their plans for their break-in at Pym Technologies and if he did, he would likely murder Hank. Lang managed to use the [[Ants]] to hide the plans while Cross invited Pym to come to the presentation for the [[Yellowjacket Suit]], which Pym agreed to.
[[File:HopeVanDyne-Cross-Phonecall.jpeg|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne comforts [[Darren Cross]]]]
Once Cross had left, they discussed what had just happened and the risks involved; van Dyne questioned whether or not Cross had known she was in the house as if he had seen her, then her position in the company would be in danger. This question was seemingly answered when Cross phoned her and asked where she was, to which she lied and said she was at her home. Cross seemed to accept this answer and told her about his intent to increase the surveillance for the Yellowjacket Suit presentation. With this now changing the details of their plan, Lang suggested that they increase their team to include his former partners-in-crime [[Luis]], [[Dave]] and [[Kurt Goreshter]], but Pym disagreed.{{Ref|AM}}

====Building the Team====
[[File:HopeVanDyne-Recruits-Gang.jpeg|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne meets [[Luis]], [[Dave]], and [[Kurt Goreshter|Goreshter]]]]
{{Quote|You know he was arrested for stealing a smoothie machine, right?"<br>"Two smoothie machines...|Hope van Dyne and [[Luis]]|Ant-Man (film)}}
Despite Pym's protests, Luis, Kurt and Dave were brought into the plan and invited to the house where van Dyne brought them coffee. Luis thanked her and commented on how unusual it was for them to be invited back to a house they just robbed; van Dyne spoke to Lang and questioned if they could handle the job which Luis and Lang insisted they could. van Dyne watched, amused, as Lang demonstrated the capabilities of the [[Ant-Man Suit]], causing Luis to flee from the room in fear when Lang jumped on his shoulder.
[[File:HopeVanDyne-Awkward-Smile.jpeg|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne and [[Scott Lang]] discuss the plan]]
They worked out a new plan which involved Luis, Kurt and Dave getting Lang into Pym Technologies through the water pipes. Luis remained confident on his role as the man on the inside posing as a security guard, excitedly commenting on how beautiful van Dyne was and mistaking her for Lang's girlfriend. Despite their enthusiasm, van Dyne and Pym remained unconvinced that the plan could be pulled off due to their unprofessionalism.{{Ref|AM}}

===[[Infiltration into Pym Technologies Headquarters|Stealing the Yellowjacket]]===
====Discovered by Darren Cross====
[[File:HopeVanDyne-BlueLighting.jpeg|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne during the heist]]
{{Quote|Darren, what are you doing?"<br>"[[Hank Pym|He]] wasn't any more capable of caring for you than he was for me."<br>"This is not who you are, it's the [[Pym Particles|particles]] altering your brain chemistry.|Hope van Dyne and [[Darren Cross]]|Ant-Man (film)}}
On the day of the Yellowjacket Suit Presentation, van Dyne arrived first at Pym Technologies and assisted Luis in gaining access to the restricted areas. Once everything was in place for Lang to enter the facility, van Dyne went to the presentation. Along the way, she was greeted by Cross, who asked how he looked in his suit.
[[File:HopeVanDyne-Hostage.jpeg|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne is taken hostage by [[Darren Cross]]]]
When Pym arrived at the building, Cross greeted him warmly and invited him and van Dyne to speak to him in private in the demonstration room. Once they were alone, Cross' guards immediately took Pym and van Dyne hostage at gunpoint. Cross revealed that he was fully aware of their plan to steal the Yellowjacket Suit and planned to kill them all for their betrayal. Cross trapped Lang within the glass enclosure and took the Yellowjacket Suit; he then welcomed [[Mitchell Carson]] into the room and introduced him as the representative from [[Hydra]], to whom he intended to sell the suit. Pym and van Dyne implored Cross to reconsider but he refused to listen.
[[File:HopeVanDyne-Threatens-Cross.jpeg|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne threatens [[Darren Cross]]]]
Cross ordered his men to execute Pym before changing his mind and deciding to kill his mentor himself. Before Cross could exact his revenge, Lang broke out of his glass enclosure and he and van Dyne began fighting Cross' guards. In the chaos, Cross was able to shoot Pym in the shoulder before escaping with the Yellowjacket Suit. With Cross' guards defeated, van Dyne and Lang rushed to Pym's aid, as he was bleeding heavily from his wound, but van Dyne ordered Lang to chase down and stop Cross before he could get away with the Yellowjacket.{{Ref|AM}}

====Saving Her Father====
[[File:HopeVanDyne-IsNotGoingToDie.jpeg|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne and [[Hank Pym]] prepare to escape]]
{{Quote|The charges are set. We've got to find a way out of here and fast."<br>"Don't worry. I'm not gonna die, and neither are you.|Hope van Dyne and [[Hank Pym]]|Ant-Man (film)}}
While Lang battled Cross, van Dyne attempted to lift Pym to safety as the entire Pym Technologies facility had been rigged to explode, but Pym knew that he would be unable to run. However, rather than accepting death and telling van Dyne to escape, Pym revealed that the [[Shrunken Tank|tank key-ring]] he carried with him at all times, was not a key-ring at all, but a USSR Tank he had shrunk down years earlier. They transformed the tank to its original size and used it to escape, smashing through the side of the building at landing outdoors, much to the alarm of everyone present.
[[File:Ant-Man (film) 45.png|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne sees [[Pym Technologies]] explode]]
Van Dyne ensured that Pym was getting medical attention from a nearby ambulance before they witnessed the entire Pym Technologies building exploding due to the C4 which Lang had planted inside. While van Dyne stayed with her father as his wound was treated, Lang tracked down and fought Cross. Eventually, Lang was able to kill Cross by damaging the internal mainframe of the latter suit's, briefly teleporting him to the [[Quantum Realm]] before he was able to return to normal size.{{Ref|AM}}

====Mission Aftermath====
[[File:ScottLang-HopevanDyne-Caught-Kissing.jpeg|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne is caught kissing [[Scott Lang]]]]
{{Quote|When did this happen?"<br>"Nothing's happening."<br>"Whoa, hold on. Something's kind of happening.|[[Hank Pym]], Hope van Dyne and [[Scott Lang]]|Ant-Man (film)}}
With the crisis now over, van Dyne and [[Hank Pym]] spoke to [[Scott Lang]] about his experiences within the [[Quantum Realm]], although he insisted that he had no memory of his experience and could tell them nothing. Van Dyne walked Lang out of the mansion, but before they could exit, Lang kissed her. The moment was interrupted when Pym walked through the door and caught them. Lang denied any wrongdoing and insisted it was van Dyne who had kissed him before making a speedy exit.{{Ref|AM}}

===Rescuing Her Mother===
====Becoming the Next Wasp====
[[File:Hope-Wasp.png|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne is given the [[Wasp Suit]]]]
{{Quote|It's about damn time.|Hope van Dyne to [[Hank Pym]]|Ant-Man (film)}}
[[Hank Pym]] revealed to van Dyne that before her [[Janet van Dyne|mother]]'s disappearance into the [[Quantum Realm]], he and Janet were working on a prototype for a new upgraded version of the [[Wasp Suit]], which had been hidden behind a secret vault in his basement for decades. Although he had always believed it had been for her mother, Pym told van Dyne that he now knew they had in fact been designing it for her. Van Dyne accepted the suit without hesitation, noting that it was about time that she was given a suit.{{Ref|AM}}

====Looking into the Quantum Realm====
[[File:Hank and Hope work together.png|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne begins to work with [[Hank Pym]]]]
{{Quote|Dad, what are you saying?"<br>"I think it's possible to bring [[Janet van Dyne|her]] back.|Hope van Dyne and [[Hank Pym]]|Ant-Man and the Wasp}}
Later on, [[Hank Pym]] revealed the full story of [[Janet van Dyne]]'s death, explaining how she became trapped in the [[Quantum Realm]], and that [[Scott Lang]] recently escaping from there had given him hope to Janet could still be alive. Pym reopened his old projects, and decided to let van Dyne in on his plans to construct a way to enter and exit the Quantum Realm, so they could search for Janet, believing that it could be possible to find her and bring her back after all these years.{{Ref|AMatW}}

====Becoming a Fugitive====
[[File:Hope in Luis' story.png|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne breaks up with [[Scott Lang]]]]
{{Quote|[[Battle at Leipzig-Halle Airport|Germany]]."<br>"What do you mean?"<br>"We were working together, training together, and other stuffing together.|Hope van Dyne and [[Scott Lang]]|Ant-Man and the Wasp}}
With both possessing their own suits, van Dyne and [[Scott Lang]] proceeded to work and train together, while still maintaining a relationship. In 2016, Lang went to [[Germany]] and took part in the [[Avengers Civil War]] and was arrested for breaking the [[Sokovia Accords]] and international laws. Offended by Lang's leaving them abruptly and not inviting her to help, van Dyne broke up with him.

Due to [[Hank Pym|Pym]]'s tech being involved, van Dyne and her father were subsequently hunted by the [[FBI]], forcing them to go into hiding and become fugitives. Despite this, van Dyne and her father were still able to continue with their project of building a [[Quantum Tunnel]], working out of a [[Mobile Laboratory|shrinkable lab building]], as well as monitoring any threats to them, mainly Lang. To acquire the needed parts for their machine, van Dyne would make several deals with black market arms dealer [[Sonny Burch]].{{Ref|AMatW}}

====Reuniting with Scott Lang====
[[File:Hope driving tiny car.png|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne kidnaps an unconscious [[Scott Lang|Lang]]]]
{{Quote|I'm sorry! All right? I didn't think I'd get caught."<br>"You didn't think about a lot of things.|[[Scott Lang]] and Hope van Dyne|Ant-Man and the Wasp}}
Immediately after van Dyne and [[Hank Pym|her father]] opened the [[Quantum Realm]] for a short period of time, they were called by [[Scott Lang]], who said he had a dream about seeing [[Janet van Dyne|her mother]]. To learn more about what he saw, van Dyne went to Lang's [[Scott Lang's House|house]], knocked him out, kidnapped him, and drove him back to the [[Mobile Laboratory|lab]] in a shrunken car, while he was unconscious.
[[File:Ant-man-and-the-wasp-paul-rudd-evangeline-lilly.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne being reunited with [[Scott Lang]]]]
When Lang woke up, Van Dyne, who was still bitter towards him, asked how certain he was that he saw her mother while in his dream of being in the Quantum Realm. Realizing he was away from his house, Lang freaked out and asked van Dyne to take him back, as he was still under house arrest. But, van Dyne informed him that she had taken care of it, posting a giant ant to wear Lang's [[Ankle Monitor]] and cover his daily activities, revealing that they had been monitoring him, as he was the biggest risk to her and Pym.
[[File:Hope still mad at Scott.png|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne continues to stay mad at [[Scott Lang|Lang]]]]
Knowing it impacted van Dyne and Pym, Lang apologized for being in the [[Avengers]]' [[Battle at Leipzig-Halle Airport|fight]] in Germany, which he tried to explain he didn't think he would get caught, but van Dyne noted that Lang didn't think about a lot of things by getting involved. Van Dyne updated Lang on how she and Pym have been living for the last two years, forced to be on the run, with no freedom, and she clarified with Lang that she didn't want an apology, just what he was in his head.
[[File:Hope Scott elevator.png|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne brings [[Scott Lang|Lang]] to the [[Mobile Laboratory|laboratory]]]]
Arriving at the lab, van Dyne enlarged the car to its normal size, and she and Lang entered the building. In the elevator, Lang attempted to offer van Dyne money to help, thinking they had nothing from looking at the building, but she declined, which Lang soon understood why once he entered the fully equipped lab. Van Dyne proceeded to lead Lang through the lab, bringing him to Pym, who was still working on the [[Quantum Tunnel]].
[[File:Ant-Man and the Wasp 133.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne informs [[Scott Lang|Lang]] of their project]]
Both van Dyne and Pym were unhappy to be seeing Lang again, so they decided to get straight into learning what he knew, with van Dyne explaining how they were building a tunnel into the Quantum Realm to find her mother. Van Dyne and Pym then revealed their theory that when they opened the tunnel, Janet entangled with Lang to send a message to them. So, Lang told them that the only thing he could remember in the dream was playing hide and seek with a girl, which van Dyne realized was from Janet's memory. 
[[File:AMATW-00595.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne learns that her [[Janet van Dyne|mother]] is still alive]]
This realization brought joy and relief to van Dyne and Pym, as they now had strong confirmation that Janet was definitely alive. Now determined to get the tunnel working as soon as possible, van Dyne noted that they needed one final piece to stop the tunnel from overloading, which was in the possession of [[Sonny Burch]]. So, they all left the building, promising to return Lang when they were finished, as they still needed to entanglement that was in his head.{{Ref|AMatW}}

====[[Battle at the Oui|Encountering the Ghost]]====
[[File:Hope meets with Burch.png|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne meeting up with [[Sonny Burch]]]]
{{Quote|[[Hank Pym|Dad]], are you seeing [[Ghost|this]]?"<br>"Hope, get out of there!|Wasp and [[Hank Pym]]|Ant-Man and the Wasp}}
They parked outside of [[Sonny Burch]]'s [[Oui|resturant]], and van Dyne left [[Hank Pym|her father]] and [[Scott Lang]] in the van to go make the deal with Burch. Continuing to use her alias (Susan) for their exchanges, van Dyne asked Burch if he had the component she needed.
[[File:Hope exposed by Burch.png|{{AltFloat}}|[[Sonny Burch]] exposes van Dyne's identity]]
However, Burch revealed to van Dyne that his informant in the [[FBI]] had exposed her true identity to him. Dropping the façade, van Dyne asked Burch what he wanted, which he explained that he knew she and Pym were building Quantum technology, and that he wanted in on it, seeing it as the future. Van Dyne rejected Burch's offers, but he refused to sell her the component, which van Dyne expressed would make things easier if he just honored his agreement.
[[File:Ant-Man and the Wasp 40.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne fighting [[Sonny Burch]]'s goons]]
Accepting Burch's refusal to cooperate, van Dyne left, and went to put on her [[Wasp Suit]]. Shrinking herself down, van Dyne proceeded to beat up Burch's goons, using a combination of her wings, [[Wasp's Stingers|stingers]], and her own superior fighting ability to do so. When the goons opened fire upon van Dyne, she hid in the chandelier, until she noticed [[Uzman]] escaping with the component, so van Dyne left her position, and followed him into the kitchen.
[[File:Ant-man-and-the-wasp-image.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne runs across a knife in mid-air]]
To stop Uzman from getting away, van Dyne used a [[Pym Particle Discs|Pym Particle Disc]] to enlarge a salt shaker, knocking him out. Another goon entered, and threw three knives at van Dyne, which she dodged by shrinking down, and even ran across the last one in mid-air. With the remaining goons, van Dyne skilfully avoided their attacks, and used her smaller size and items in the kitchen to knock them all out. Having won the fight, van Dyne took the component, left the money for Burch, and went to leave.
[[File:Ant-Man and the Wasp 110.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne prepares to fight against [[Ghost]]]]
But before van Dyne could get to the door, she noticed a [[Ghost|mysterious figure]] appear in front of her, and then subsequently disappear, so van Dyne readied herself for another fight. Being able to become invisible and intangible, Ghost attempted to steal the component from van Dyne. Pym told his daughter to get herself away from Ghost, but she was unable to, and had to keep fighting. Lang soon arrived and helped van Dyne, but they lost Ghost.
[[File:USTODAY Ant-Man-and-Wasp.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne learns [[Ghost]] stole the [[Mobile Laboratory|Mobile Lab]]]]
They realized that Ghost had gone after Pym, so van Dyne and Lang shrunk themselves down, and rushed back to the van. Once they got back, they found that Pym was still alive, but he told them that Ghost had stolen the miniature lab, much to their frustration, as it set back their entire project. Driving away from the scene, they discussed Ghost, not knowing what it was, and decided that they needed to find a place to regroup and figure out where to find the lab. With a shortage of option, Lang suggested that they head to the [[X-Con Security Consultants Office]].
[[File:Ant-Man and the Wasp 149.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne discusses finding the [[Mobile Laboratory|Mobile Lab]]]]
Once again finding themselves reunited with [[Luis]], [[Dave]] and [[Kurt Goreshter]], van Dyne and Pym were annoyed as the three and Lang bickered with each other, when they had bigger things to be dealing with. They all then discussed Ghost, noting its ability to phase, and van Dyne brought up the idea of tracking the lab's radiation with a quantum spectrometer. No longer having access to their equipment, Pym begrudgingly revealed that his former colleague [[Bill Foster]] could help them.{{Ref|AMatW}}

====Reclaiming the Mobile Laboratory====
[[File:Hats & Sunglasses.png|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne, [[Hank Pym|Pym]] and [[Scott Lang|Lang]] see [[Bill Foster]]]]
{{Quote|I didn't come [[University of California, Berkeley|here]] to listen to you [[Hank Pym|two]] squabble. I'm trying to save my [[Janet van Dyne|mother]].|Hope van Dyne to [[Bill Foster]]|Ant-Man and the Wasp}}
Traveling to [[University of California, Berkeley]], the trio made their way through the campus, disguising themselves with hats and sunglasses, which [[Scott Lang]] noted would not stop anyone from recognizing them. They soon found [[Bill Foster]], who was giving a lecture, but he finished when he discovered their presence.
[[File:Ant-Man and the Wasp 100.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne asks [[Bill Foster|Foster]] to help find their [[Mobile Laboratory|lab]]]]
In Foster's office, they filled him in on their situation, but he was unable to help find their [[Mobile Laboratory|lab]], as he didn't have the equipment to do so. When Lang and Foster got sidetracked about Lang growing to the size of a giant in [[Germany]], van Dyne tried to get them focused on the matter at hand, but the feud between Foster and [[Hank Pym]] caused the former partners to fight. The [[FBI]] arrived, so as they went to leave, Foster gave them an idea on how to track the lab.
[[File:Hope van Dyne (Surprised at Scott Lang).png|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne learns [[Scott Lang|Lang]] preserved the [[Ant-Man Suit|suit]]]]
As they drove away, Pym ranted about his detest towards Foster, but van Dyne was confident in his idea to modify the diffraction units on a regulator. However, Pym's upgrades to the [[Ant-Man Suit|su]][[Wasp Suit|its]] eliminated the regulators, meaning they still couldn't track down the lab. Lang revealed that he didn't destroy his old suit he used when [[Battle at Leipzig-Halle Airport|fighting]] with the [[Avengers]] after he was arrested, but instead kept it hidden, which he lied about to them earlier.
[[File:Ant-Man and the Wasp EW.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne and [[Scott Lang]] fly in the [[Brookemont Elementary School|school]]]]
After checking with [[Luis]] about the suit, Lang discovered that it was no longer at his [[Scott Lang's House|house]], but soon realized it was at his [[Cassie Lang|daughter]]'s [[Brookemont Elementary School|school]]. Arriving at Cassie's school, van Dyne and Lang suited up so they could sneak into it and steal the previous Ant-Man suit that was in Lang's trophy from Cassie. After shrinking themselves down so they could stealthily fly through the school, Lang's suit began to malfunction, due to it still being worked on by Pym, and not completed, causing Lang to grow, but not to his full size.
[[File:Ant-Man and the Wasp 153.png|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne teasing [[Scott Lang]] about his size]]
When children were coming out of their classes, Lang and van Dyne hid in the closet and she witnessed as he then grew, no longer fitting in the room, much to van Dyne's amusement. She then inspected Lang's belt, and attempted to fix it, but was only able to revert him back to his normal size for a moment, before he shrunk down again. Seeing levity in Lang's problem, van Dyne teased him about it, jokingly saying if [[Steve Rogers|Captain America]] could only see him now.
[[File:Van Dyne & Pym find the lab.png|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne rejoices in tracking down the [[Mobile Laboratory|lab]]]]
Unable to fix Lang's suit, van Dyne gave Lang a hoodie to disguise him as a child, so they could proceed with the mission. Reaching Cassie's classroom, van Dyne continued to tease Lang about his current problem, as he couldn't reach the top shelf. Acquiring the suit, van Dyne and Lang made their escape, and returned to the van, where she was joined by Pym in making fun of Lang. Using the regulator's diffraction units, they were able to track down the lab.
[[File:AMATW Stills 01.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne and [[Scott Lang]] discuss [[Battle at Leipzig-Halle Airport|Germany]]]]
Arriving at the [[Ghost's Hideout|location]] of the lab, van Dyne and Lang suited up once more so they could steal it back, and prepare for another fight to possibly occur. As they got ready, Lang happily acknowledged how he and van Dyne had teamed up twice on the same day, leading van Dyne to reflect on their former relationship and what it would be like now if Lang hadn't left her to go to Germany. Lang then asked van Dyne if she would have come with him if he had asked, which she replied that they'll never know, but she could guarantee that if she did, he wouldn't have been arrested. Van Dyne then shrunk herself down, and flew out of the van, heading for the hideout.
[[File:WaspLookingAtGhostSuit-Flying.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne sess [[Ghost]] sleeping in a [[Quantum Energy Chamber|chamber]]]]
As van Dyne and Lang infiltrated the hideout, Pym informed them that he wasn't picking up anything on the monitors due to an electronic disturbance, so they had to be careful. The two discovered [[Ghost]]  sleeping inside a [[Quantum Energy Chamber|chamber]], away from her suit, so they decided to hurry while she was still asleep. They found the lab, but when they enlarged to take it, van Dyne quickly noticed that Ghost was now gone from the chamber. Before either of them could act, Ghost appeared and knocked the two out.
[[File:Scott, Hope & Hank tied up.png|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne learns about [[Ava Starr]]'s problem]]
Ghost also knocked Pym unconscious, and the three were tied up together. Van Dyne and Pym were woken up by Ghost, who was named Ava Starr, and they discovered that Foster was working with her. Starr revealed that Pym had fired her [[Elihas Starr|father]], which resulted in not only her parent's deaths, but also rendered her in a permanently unstable state. Since then, Starr and Foster had been trying to find a cure, only to discover what they had been [[Quantum Tunnel|working on]].
[[File:Hope steals lab back.png|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne steals back the [[Mobile Laboratory]]]]
Foster proceeded to explain that from learning about Lang's entanglement with [[Janet van Dyne]], they could extract quantum energy and use it to repair Starr's molecular structure. However, this would kill Janet in the process, which they could not allow Starr and Foster to do, so Pym faked a heart attack to stop them. Van Dyne was in on it, so she begged Foster to open the Altoids tin, allowing giant ants to burst out and free them. Van Dyne defeated Starr with her [[Wasp's Stingers|stingers]] and stole the lab back, and the three made their escape.{{Ref|AMatW}}

====Locating Her Mother====
[[File:Team Ant repair Quantum Tunnel.png|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne helps repair the [[Quantum Tunnel]]]]
{{Quote|You'd think with all this time to prepare I'd be more ready."<br>"Oh, going subatomic isn't something you can prepare for. It kind of melts your mind."<br>"I mean seeing my [[Janet van Dyne|mom]] again.|Hope van Dyne and [[Scott Lang]]|Ant-Man and the Wasp}}
Heading to the [[Muir Woods]], the three enlarged the [[Mobile Laboratory]] and began fixing the [[Quantum Tunnel]], so they could be ready to open it up again.
[[File:Hope nervous about seeing her mother again.png|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne is comforted about her [[Janet van Dyne|mother]]]]
As van Dyne and [[Scott Lang]] adjusted the relays, van Dyne expressed her nervousness about not being ready, which Lang thought was about going subatomic. However, van Dyne corrected him in that it was about seeing her [[Janet van Dyne|mother]] again after all this time. Van Dyne worried if her mother was going to be a different person, or worse, not even remember her, but Lang comforted her, revealing how he never forgot about his [[Cassie Lang|daughter]] when in prison.
[[File:Ant-Man and the Wasp 10.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne and [[Hank Pym]] open the [[Quantum Tunnel|Tunnel]]]]
Once they were ready, van Dyne and [[Hank Pym]] activated the Tunnel, telling Lang to be ready for any sort of message Janet may send him. Unfortunately their celebration was cut short when the Tunnel suddenly stopped, so van Dyne and Pym tried to find the problem. They noticed Lang using the computer, but soon realized it was actually Janet possessing his body. Shocked to be reunited with her mother, van Dyne watched as Janet began fixing the Tunnel.
[[File:Janet using Scott's body to work.png|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne briefly reunited with her [[Janet van Dyne|mother]]]]
Van Dyne figured out that Janet had put an antenna in Lang's head, and she continued to watch as her mother helped her family track her down in the Quantum Realm. They were soon able to successfully locate Janet, and she told her family to find her within the next two hours, otherwise she'll be lost for an entire century. Van Dyne promised her mother that she would find her, and they prepared to enter the Quantum Realm.{{Ref|AMatW}}

====[[Arrest of Hank Pym and Hope van Dyne|Arrested]]====
[[File:Ant-Man and the Wasp 141.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne is told the [[FBI]] know their location]]
{{Quote|Scott?"<br>"What're you [[Hank Pym|two]] just standing around for? We gotta go find that [[Mobile Laboratory|lab]].|Hope van Dyne and [[Scott Lang]]|Ant-Man and the Wasp}}
Before they could enter the [[Quantum Realm]], [[Scott Lang]] informed van Dyne and [[Hank Pym]] that [[Ghost]] and the [[FBI]] knew their location and were coming soon, forcing them to shut down the [[Quantum Tunnel]]. As van Dyne and Pym were doing so, Lang, who they were mad at, had to leave and return to his [[Scott Lang's House|house]].
[[File:Ant-Man and the Wasp 13.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|The [[FBI]] arrest van Dyne and [[Hank Pym]]]]
Once they shut everything down, van Dyne and Pym exited the [[Mobile Laboratory]] and went to relocate. But, when Pym shrunk the lab down, they found themselves surrounded by FBI agents, and the father and daughter were then arrested. Before they were driven away, van Dyne and Pym overheard agents mention that an [[Stoltz|agent]] was killed and that the lab was missing, which they realized was Ghost. The two were then taken into FBI custody, where they were told they'd have to wait an hour, which they did not have.
[[File:Hope rescued by Scott.png|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne is impressed by [[Scott Lang|Lang]]'s rescue]]
Fortunately, van Dyne had hidden a hairpin in her mouth, which she used to free her and Pym from their handcuffs. Van Dyne had also snuck a [[Pym Particle Discs|Pym Particle Disc]], which she intended to use to shrink a wall and make their escape, despite their bad odds. But before they could, van Dyne's [[Wasp Suit]] appeared, which was because Lang had come to rescue them. Van Dyne suited up, and she and Pym managed to escape the FBI's custody, joining Lang in their van.{{Ref|AMatW}}

====[[Chase for the Mobile Laboratory]]====
[[File:Hope Hank and Scott AMATW.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne, [[Hank Pym|Pym]] and [[Scott Lang|Lang]] formulate a plan]]
{{Quote|In case I don't make it back..."<br>"Don't. Don't say that. I can't lose you, too."<br>"I love you, Hope.|[[Hank Pym]] and Wasp|Ant-Man and the Wasp}}
As they drove away, [[Hank Pym]] revealed that he had put a new tracker on the [[Mobile Laboratory]], and he communicated with [[Ants]] to guide them to its location. Finding the lab, the three discussed the plan, noting that they didn't have long before [[Janet van Dyne]]'s location would shift. As [[Scott Lang]] attempted to make a plan, Pym said he would be the one entering the [[Quantum Realm]], so van Dyne and Lang could fight [[Ghost]] and protect him.
[[File:Ant-Man and the Wasp 132.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Wasp is complimented on her [[Wasp Suit|suit]] by [[Luis]]]]
The three were joined by [[Luis]], who was stationed with Wasp in the van, as they waited for the ants to disable the [[Quantum Tunnel]]. Luis complimented Wasp's [[Wasp Suit|suit]], expressing how he wished he had one. They were then notified by Pym that Ghost and [[Bill Foster]] had been drawn away from the lab, allowing him to enter the Quantum Realm. Before Pym went in, he told Wasp he loved her, in case he didn't make it back, and she then shrunk the lab and drove away with it.
[[File:Ant-Man and the Wasp 93.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Wasp tactically defeats [[Sonny Burch]]'s fleet]]
Having retrieved the lab, Wasp and Luis went to meet up with Ant-Man at the rendezvous point, but were stopped when [[Sonny Burch]] and his goons pulled up in front of them. With their plans changed, Wasp engaged in a chase with Burch, using the van's shrinking capabilities to maneuver and take out his fleet of cars. Leading Burch's goons to {{WPS|Lombard Street (San Francisco)|Lombard Street}}, Wasp was able to take out the remainder of the cars.
[[File:Wasp enlarges Pez dispenser.png|{{AltFloat}}|Wasp fires [[Pym Particle Discs|discs]] upon [[Sonny Burch]]'s goons]]
Ant-Man joined them in the van, but when more goons approached on motorbikes, Wasp decided to deal with them herself. Wasp fired a [[Pym Particle Discs|Pym Particle Disc]] from her [[Wasp's Stingers|stingers]] to shrink one of the goon's bike, but was unable to get the others due to the van's unsteadiness. So, Wasp threw Luis' {{WPS|Pez}} dispenser out and enlarged it, knocking out the remaining goons on bikes. But, Ghost had found them, and she phased inside the van, kicking Wasp out and stealing the lab.
[[File:Ant-man-and-the-wasp-ghost4.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Wasp and [[Ant-Man]] fighting against [[Ghost]]]]
Wasp managed to follow Ghost, who had stolen a truck, so she flew down to her, and entered the vehicle. Growing full size, Wasp and Ghost fought each other, both using their own abilities to avoid each other's attacks, until they were joined by Ant-Man, who grew himself, and punched Ghost in the face. This caused her to lose the lab, which Wasp went after, but Ghost followed her. Before the two went to continue fighting, Burch drove up behind them, knocking Wasp backwards, allowing Burch to steal the lab and drive away.
[[File:Ant-Man and the Wasp 131.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Wasp fighting against [[Sonny Burch]]'s goons]]
Burch and his goons began chasing Luis, as he had the remote for the lab, so Wasp pursued them to save Luis. Breaking into the car that was going after Luis, Wasp once again used her superior skills to fight and knock out each of the goons in the car, causing it to crash. Running out of time, Wasp then joined up again with Luis in his car, and they went to meet up with Ant-Man, who went to steal back the lab from Burch, who was attempting to get away.
[[File:Wasp saves Ant-Man from drowning.png|{{AltFloat}}|Wasp trying to save [[Ant-Man]] from drowning]]
Arriving at the docks, Wasp and Luis discovered Ant-Man in his giant form, which she realized was making him exhausted, as they witnessed him pass out and fall into the ocean. Wasp told Luis to get the lab somewhere safe, as she went to save Ant-Man before he drowned, due to the suit not having enough air. Wasp dove into the water and attempted to wake Ant-Man up, but failed, so she repaired his regulator, causing him to shrink.
[[File:Hope kissing Scott Lang.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Wasp passionately kissing [[Ant-Man]]]]
Desperately searching through in the water, Wasp managed to locate Ant-Man, grabbed him, and carried him out of the water, so he could get some air. Wasp then brought the unconscious Ant-Man to the surface and grew him back to his normal size. Soon, Ant-Man awoke, much to Wasp's relief, as she then immediately and passionately kissed him.{{Ref|AMatW}}

====Reunited with Her Mother====
[[File:Ant-man-and-the-wasp-evangeline-lilly-paul-rudd.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Wasp and [[Ant-Man]] arrive to stop [[Ghost]]]]
{{Quote|We found you. I missed you so much."<br>"I missed you too, Jellybean.|Wasp and [[Janet van Dyne]]|Ant-Man and the Wasp}}
Wasp and [[Ant-Man]] then rushed into the [[Mobile Laboratory]], which had been enlarged to stop [[Ghost]] from disrupting their plans. Reaching the [[Quantum Tunnel]], the two noticed that Ghost had already started to extract the energy from the [[Quantum Realm]], so they disabled her [[Quantum Energy Chamber]] so that [[Janet van Dyne]] wouldn't be torn apart.
[[File:Scott saving Hope.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Wasp is saved by [[Ant-Man]] from being hit]]
While Wasp was fixing the Tunnel, Ghost knocked away Ant-Man, and was heading for her, so Wasp attempted to fire her [[Wasp's Stingers|stingers]] at Ghost to keep her away, but she phased through them. Wasp then engaged Ghost in hand-to-hand, soon joined by Ant-Man, and the two partners overpowered their opponent using teamwork. But, Wasp was soon knocked down by Ghost, right as [[Quantum Vehicle]] returned, which was going to drive through Wasp and Ghost. So, Ant-Man grew himself and saved Wasp before she would be hit.
[[File:Wasp-JvanDyne-Hug&aKiss.png|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne is finally reunited with her [[Janet van Dyne|mother]]]]
The Quantum Vehicle crashed, knocking Ghost away, and van Dyne and Lang witnessed as Janet stepped out of it. The mother and daughter became overwhelmed with emotions and hugged each other upon finally being reunited. Van Dyne told her mother that she missed her so much, which she reciprocated, calling her by her nickname, Jellybean. [[Hank Pym]] came out of the wreckage, so Wasp went to hug him, being glad that he was safe, too.
[[File:Group leaves the area.png|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne and her allies make their escape]]
Suddenly, Ghost got back up, so van Dyne went to deal with her, but was stopped by her mother. They all watched as Janet approached Ghost and held her face, using her powers to temporarily heal her. [[Luis]] then entered the lab, revealing that the police were on their way to their location. To distract the [[FBI]], Lang planted his [[Ant-Man Suit|suit]] in its giant form to lead them away, and van Dyne recovered it, once they were able to shrink the lab. and they escaped in [[Luis' Van]].{{Ref|AMatW}}

===[[Infinity War]]===
====Partners Again====
[[File:Tiny Drive In.png|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne meets [[Cassie Lang]]]]
{{Quote|I wanted to be [[Ant-Man|his]] partner. But he said he wants you."<br>"Is that so?|[[Cassie Lang]] and Hope van Dyne|Ant-Man and the Wasp}}
With [[Scott Lang]] no longer under house arrest, and her feelings about him being changed, van Dyne decided to resume her relationship with him. One night, van Dyne joined Lang and his daughter, [[Cassie Lang]] in a shrunken car to watch a {{WPS|Them! (1954 film)|movie}} from a laptop, and she asked Cassie what she wanted to be when she grew up, which she responded that she wanted to help people like her father. Cassie then revealed that Lang wanted van Dyne to be his partner, which made her happy.{{Ref|AMatW}}

Although together for the long haul, as van Dyne and Lang continued to work together as partners, they would occasionally have some troubles, both in their relationship and while fighting supervillains. Sometimes the two aspects would crossover, and they would let pent-up problems spill into life-or-death situations. During one of their missions, they were both unable to use their resizing controls and were about to be killed by a set of mechanical gears. Van Dyne berated Lang that they could have easily escaped if he loaded a magnetized grappling hook. They survived the situation, but from this, they both learned that while it's easy to lash out with each other because they know the other can take it, they should try not to say anything they might regret, considering that it could be the last thing either of them say due to the dangerousness of being a superhero.

Having made this positive adjustment to their relationship, van Dyne and Lang became more in sync, developing their own secret language comprised of shorthand, absurd nicknames, shared references, and inside jokes, which have assisted in situations when time was limited. This synchrony also developed into combat, as they would be able to fight alongside each other optimally without even needing to verbally communicate. Because being superheroes consumed most of their days, van Dyne and Lang would appreciate the time they could have together just at home doing normal things, which for van Dyne included letting her guard down and getting passionately hooked on a dating game show, and for Lang it was playing video games, which van Dyne struggled with. Flourishing as both lovers and fighters, van Dyne and Lang were given a good perspective on life's priorities, as whenever they would come home, it would be the best feeling because they were together.{{Ref|LOftLG}}

====[[Snap]]====
[[File:Van Dyne Quantum Energy Collector.png|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne prepares [[Scott Lang]] for his task]]
{{Quote|Preparing for re-entry in five... four... three-|Hope Van Dyne to [[Scott Lang]]|Ant-Man and the Wasp}}
Van Dyne and her family kept their promise to [[Ava Starr]] and they built a smaller [[Quantum Tunnel]] in [[Luis' Van]], where they planned to harvest Quantum energy to make a cure. Lang was set to enter the [[Quantum Realm]], so van Dyne gave him the [[Quantum Energy Collector]] she had been working on, and informed him how it worked.
[[File:Janet, Hope & Hank Death.png|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne is a victim of the [[Snap]]]]
She joined her parents as they stood by and counted down Lang's entry. Once he finished collecting, he notified van Dyne who began to count down his re-entry, when suddenly she, along with her parents, [[Snap|disintegrated]].{{Ref|AMatW}}

====[[Battle of Earth]]====
[[File:Wasp (Endgame).png|{{AltFloat}}|Wasp joining the [[Battle of Earth|battle]]]]
{{Quote|Get [[Quantum Tunnel|it]] started, we'll get the [[Infinity Stones|stones]] to you."<br>"[[Ant-Man|We]]'re on it, Cap.|[[Steve Rogers|Captain America]] and Wasp|Avengers: Endgame}}
[[2023|Five years later]], as a result of the [[Blip]], van Dyne was restored to life. She was then contacted by the [[Masters of the Mystic Arts]] to help fight in the [[Battle of Earth|battle]] against an [[Thanos/Cosmic Time Heist|alternate Thanos]] and his army. She [[Wasp Suit|suited up]] as the Wasp and flew through a [[Inter-Dimensional Portal|portal]] opened up for her, teleporting her to the ruins of the [[Avengers Compound]]. 
[[File:Endgame 77.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Wasp stands with the assembled heroes]]
She then stood alongside the assembled heroes as [[Steve Rogers]] proceeded to lead the charge. She shrunk down and flew at the [[Chitauri|alien]] army, using her [[Wasp's Stingers|stingers]] to take them out, as well as her combat abilities when resuming normal size.
[[File:Wasp carrying Ant-Man 1.png|{{AltFloat}}|Wasp flies while carrying [[Ant-Man]]]]
Eventually, van Dyne met with Lang, but was unable to have a real reunion with him, as Rogers told them they would bring the [[Nano Gauntlet]] to them. Van Dyne confirmed they'd get it done, calling him "Cap," just like Lang and they shared a smile with each other. 
[[File:A-Force.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Wasp helps [[Captain Marvel]] during the [[Battle of Earth|fight]]]]
Van Dyne and Lang shrunk themselves down, and van Dyne carried Lang to Luis' van. Once they arrived at the van, they sat in the front seats, and began activating the Quantum Tunnel, which required Lang to hot-wire the van. Afterwards, van Dyne returned to the battle and joined [[Captain Marvel]], who was tasked with carrying the Gauntlet, and other female heroes as they faced off against a horde of the army.
[[File:Avengers Endgame - Shuri Rescue Wasp.png|{{AltFloat}}|Wasp, [[Pepper Potts]], and [[Shuri]] fight [[Thanos/Cosmic Time Heist|Thanos]]]]
As Danvers neared the van, alternate Thanos charged her, but was stopped by the combined blasts from van Dyne, [[Rescue|Pepper Potts]], and [[Shuri]], knocking him down. However, alternate Thanos used his [[Double-Edged Sword|sword]] to destroy the van. The battle concluded when [[Tony Stark]] stole the Infinity Stones and used them to wipe out alternate Thanos and his army, which cost him his own life.{{Ref|AE}}
[[File:Hope-Scott-Cassie.png|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne sits with [[Ant-Man|Scott]] and [[Cassie Lang]]]]
All the heroes, including van Dyne, knelt before Stark, out of respect for his sacrifice.{{Ref|AEDS}} After the battle, van Dyne and Lang returned to [[San Francisco]] and went to [[Jim Paxton's House]] to have a real reunion together with [[Cassie Lang|Cassie]], who was now five years older. The three sat outside together and watched the fireworks going off to celebrate the return of people following the Blip. 
[[File:Janet van Dyne (Endgame).png|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne attends the funeral of [[Tony Stark]]]]
A few days later, despite only just meeting him as an ally in battle, van Dyne, along with her restored [[Hank Pym|par]][[Janet van Dyne|ents]] and Lang, attended Stark's funeral at his [[Stark Eco-Compound|home]]. The four stood together and watched Potts and her [[Morgan Stark|daughter]] walk to the lake, where they placed Stark's [[Arc Reactor]], sending it adrift.{{Ref|AE}} Following her role in the battle, van Dyne became known to the [[Earth|world]] as the superhero Wasp.{{Ref|MM101}}

=== Back from the Snap ===
====Helping the World====
[[File:CEO Wasp.png|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne at the [[Pym van Dyne Foundation]]]]
{{Quote|Reforestation, affordable housing, food production, she's not wasting a second.|[[Scott Lang]]|Ant-Man and the Wasp: Quantumania}}
Although [[Thanos/Cosmic Time Heist|Thanos]] was defeated, the [[Blip]] had sustained aftereffects, so van Dyne dedicated herself to helping the [[Earth|world]]. She started by taking back her [[Hank Pym|father]]'s [[Pym Technologies|company]], renaming it the [[Pym van Dyne Foundation]] and under van Dyne's leadership, turned the focus towards using [[Pym Particles]] for global change.
[[File:Wasp wins an award.png|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne wins the [[Humanitarian Global Services Award|Humanitarian Award]]]]
The foundation, was successful in its efforts to positively impact the world, including renewing the forests, creating affordable housing options and increasing the production of food. Van Dyne's altruism resulted in her receiving the [[Humanitarian Global Services Award]]. Van Dyne's partnership with [[Scott Lang]] continued to flourish, both romantically and as Ant-Man and Wasp. She also began to grow close with [[Cassie Lang]], becoming a mother-figure to her and aiding her in her research into the [[Quantum Realm]].{{Ref|AMatWQ}}

====Interview for a Memoir====
{{Quote|So to make sure I'm getting the story straight, I'm sitting down with Hope to hear, and share, her take on what happened.|[[Scott Lang]]|Look Out for the Little Guy!}}
In [[2024]], [[Scott Lang]] was chosen to write a book about the events around the [[Blip]], however, he decided to also make it about his life. This included detailing his relationship with van Dyne. However, knowing that van Dyne had her own experience of their time together, Lang thought it was best to interview her for complete accuracy. Van Dyne provided her own perspective on Lang [[Battle at Leipzig-Halle Airport|leaving]] to fight alongside [[Steve Rogers|Captain America]]'s [[Avengers]], their reunion during his house arrest, and the mission to save her [[Janet van Dyne|mother]].{{Ref|LOftLG}}

===Adventure in the Quantum Realm===
====Family Dinner====
[[File:Hope, Cassie & Scott.png|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne discussing [[Cassie Lang]]'s actions]]
{{Quote|I missed this."<br>"No pizza in the [[Quantum Realm]]?"<br>"No. No anything.|[[Janet van Dyne]] and Hope van Dyne|Ant-Man and the Wasp: Quantumania}}
When [[Cassie Lang]] was arrested, van Dyne was contacted by the San Francisco County Jail, so she came down to bail her daughter-figure out. [[Scott Lang]] arrived shortly after van Dyne, and they picked up Cassie. As they drove to the [[Pym Residence]], Scott and Cassie talked about what happened; with van Dyne noting that; Scott was trying to tell his daughter what to do.
[[File:Wasp asks about the QR.png|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne asking about the [[Quantum Realm]]]]
Arriving at her parent's house for a family dinner, van Dyne once again approached her [[Janet van Dyne|mother]] about wanting to talk about her time in the [[Quantum Realm]]. But Janet stated that; she spent too much of her life down there and now just wanted to be in the present. As they ate, van Dyne and her parents teased Scott for how he was profiting off of his role in [[Battle of Earth|saving the world]]. Lang then discovered that van Dyne and [[Hank Pym]] had been working with Cassie, so they decided to show him what they were building.
[[File:Quantumania Trailer (19).png|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne talks about the [[Quantum Satellite]]]]
They went down to Pym's lab, where they revealed that; they had been studying the Quantum Realm. Janet enquired as to why she wasn't asked to consult on it, but van Dyne reminded her that; she had asked multiple times. Janet insisted that the Quantum Realm was dangerous, so van Dyne assured her mother that they would not be going inside it, leading to Cassie revealing the [[Quantum Satellite]] they built. But, upon learning a signal was being sent to the Quantum Realm, Janet forcibly turned it off, much to everyone's confusion.{{Ref|AMatWQ}}

====Trapped in the Quantum Realm====
[[File:Wasp flies into the QR.png|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne flying straight into the portal]]
{{Quote|You said there was nothing down [[Quantum Realm|here]]. Why didn't you tell us about all of this?"<br>"Hope, I will explain everything, but right now I just need you to trust me."<br>"Then make me trust you!|Hope van Dyne and [[Janet van Dyne]]|Ant-Man and the Wasp: Quantumania}}
[[Janet van Dyne]] went to explain herself, but the [[Quantum Satellite]] reactivated and a blue wave of energy was released. A small portal then opened and began to suck in everything in the lab, so the family held on as the portal grew stronger and tried to pull them in. [[Hank Pym]] and Janet fell into the portal, so van Dyne gave [[Scott Lang]] a knowing look that she was going in after her parents. She changed into her [[Wasp Suit]] and dove straight into the portal.
[[File:Wasp in the QR.png|{{AltFloat}}|Wasp finds herself in the [[Quantum Realm]]]]
Van Dyne managed to grab both of her parents, and the landed in a jungle-like environment inside of the [[Quantum Realm]]. Van Dyne regrouped with her father, who wondered why they weren't dead, and as they called out to Janet, they spotted a vehicle scanning the area. Janet appeared and moved van Dyne and Pym into cover so that they wouldn't be detected. Once they were clear, Janet told them that they needed to find Scott and [[Cassie Lang]], so they began to make their way through the Quantum Realm.
[[File:PymVanDyne Family.png|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne questions her [[Janet van Dyne|mother]]'s secrets]]
As they walked, van Dyne and Pym questioned Janet on what they hid from, having been told that there was nothing in the Quantum Realm. Janet promised to fill them in once they were safe, but van Dyne continued to confront her mother. Pym tried to ease the tension, but Janet snapped at them for not telling her they were studying the Quantum Realm. Agreeing to focus on finding Scott and Cassie and getting home, they proceeded out of the jungle, with Janet describing the Quantum Realm as a secret universe outside of time and space.{{Ref|AMatWQ}}

====Exploring the Quantum Realm====
[[File:Wasp battle stance.png|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne watches her [[Janet van Dyne|mother]] fighting]]
{{Quote|So, what's your story then?"<br>"Oh, god.|[[Broccoli Man]] and Hope van Dyne|Ant-Man and the Wasp: Quantumania}}
The three were found by large group of people, so van Dyne readied herself for a fight, but [[Janet van Dyne]] told them she would handle it. Van Dyne and [[Hank Pym]] watched as Janet walked up to the group's leader and stabbed him. However, they discovered that Janet was friends with the group, and they were provided with transportation and disguises. Janet told them that they were going to speak with an old [[Krylar|friend]] of her who would know where [[Scott Lang|Scott]] and [[Cassie Lang]] are.
[[File:Hank, Janet and Hope.png|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne and her [[Hank Pym|par]][[Janet van Dyne|ents]] exploring [[Axia]]]]
They rode on a creature that brought them to [[Axia]], a vastly populated city inside of the [[Quantum Realm]]. As they walked through the streets, van Dyne noticed some soldiers abusing a civilian, but Janet told her to just keep her head down, as she led them to a secret door. Inside was a bar filled with different kinds of creatures, and Janet made van Dyne and Pym drink an ooze which allowed them to understand the civilians. As they waited at the bar for Janet, van Dyne was hit on by one of the patrons.{{Ref|AMatWQ}}

====[[Ambush in Axia|Encounter with Krylar]]====
[[File:Wasp meets Krylar.png|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne witnesses the arrival of [[Krylar]]]]
{{Quote|Hope? You have to be Hope. She talked about you every day."<br>"That's strange, she never said anything about you.|[[Krylar]] and Hope van Dyne|Ant-Man and the Wasp: Quantumania}}
[[Janet van Dyne]] retrieved van Dyne and [[Hank Pym]] and they were shown to a table. Van Dyne asked her mother how she knew [[Krylar]], so she revealed that they were both [[Freedom Fighters]] in the [[Quantum Realm]]. Krylar arrived in his ship, and reunited with Janet, revealing that he knew about Pym and van Dyne, although van Dyne commented on her mother never mentioning him.
[[File:Wasp learns of Krylar's betrayal.png|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne learns [[Krylar]] has betrayed them]]
They all sat down, and Janet asked for Krylar's help, but he began ordering items to be brought to the table, including a drink with a scared creature inside the glass. Suddenly, a group of armed soldiers entered the bar, but Krylar ordered them to stand down and let them talk. Krylar then brought up Janet's past in the Quantum Realm, saying that she was full of secrets, but van Dyne believed he was lying. Janet begged Krylar to let her family go free, but he didn't allow it, and revealed that a [[M.O.D.O.K.|hunter]] had been sent after Scott and Cassie.
[[File:Wasp Stinger.png|{{AltFloat}}|Wasp escaping from the Quantumnauts]]
Angered by this, Wasp activated her [[Wasp's Stingers|Stingers]], preparing for a fight, but her father got her to hold off from attacking. Krylar declared that their talk was finished, so Wasp blasted two soldiers on either side of her, shrunk down and knocked out another. Krylar's Valet shot at Wasp, but in her smaller size, was able to dodge the blasts and knock him out. They then ran to Krylar's ship, and Wasp gave her parents cover as they got it started. As the ship flew away, Wasp entered the ship and uncomfortably listened to her parents discuss their sexual history.{{Ref|AMatWQ}}

====Learning about Kang====
[[File:Quantumania Trailer (39).png|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne asks her [[Janet van Dyne|mother]] about her past]]
{{Quote|I just wanted to forget. I just wanted to be your mom again."<br>"I am so sorry you had to go through all of that alone. But you are not alone now. We'll stop [[Kang the Conqueror|him]] together.|[[Janet van Dyne]] and Hope van Dyne|Ant-Man and the Wasp: Quantumania}}
Van Dyne asked her [[Janet van Dyne|mother]] what was sent after [[Scott Lang|Scott]] and [[Cassie Lang]], stressing that they needed to rescue them, but Janet was still withholding, claiming that there was something she needed to do first. Van Dyne called out her mother for still keeping secrets from them, but she responded that she was only protecting them.
[[File:Hank and Wasp learn the truth.png|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne is told about [[Kang the Conqueror]]]]
No longer wanting to have secrets between them, Janet decided to tell van Dyne and [[Hank Pym]] about her time in the [[Quantum Realm]], revealing that she was stranded with another person named [[Kang]], who claimed to be a traveler that crashed off course, and together they worked on repairing his [[Time Sphere]], only for Janet to discover that he had actually been exiled and was a conqueror of timelines. Janet explained how she stopped him from escaping, and spent her life fighting him until they rescued her.
[[File:Hope QM.png|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne comforting her [[Janet van Dyne|mother]]]]
Feeling responsible for Kang's rise to power in the Quantum Realm, Janet felt she didn't deserve to leave while he continued his reign, which was why she was closed off when van Dyne would ask her questions, as she just wanted to put it behind her and be her mother. Van Dyne comforted her mother and told her that they would stop Kang. Janet informed them that Kang needed [[Pym Particles]] to reclaim the [[Multiversal Engine Core]], which he now had access to with Scott and Cassie, so Janet made it clear to van Dyne that Kang could not escape.{{Ref|AMatWQ}}

====[[Theft of the Multiversal Engine Core]]====
[[File:Wasp in flight.png|{{AltFloat}}|Wasp flying into the [[Multiversal Engine Core]]]] 
{{Quote|Hope, are you real?"<br>"I'm real."<br>"Then let's do this.|[[Ant-Man]] and Wasp|Ant-Man and the Wasp: Quantumania}}
They arrived at the enlarged [[Multiversal Engine Core]], and Wasp managed to regain contact with [[Ant-Man]], so she flew into the core to rescue him. As Wasp went smaller and deeper inside the core, other versions of her began to form, so [[Janet van Dyne]] explained that they were just possibilities of herself. 
[[File:Wasp in Quantum Realm.png|{{AltFloat}}|Wasp rescues [[Ant-Man]] inside of the core]]
Ignoring her possible selves, Wasp continued to search for Ant-Man in the core, and she soon found him falling down towards a near infinite sea of himself, so she grabbed him. Ant-Man asked if she was real, and Wasp confirmed she was, which allowed him to refocus his mind and they eliminated all of the possible versions of themselves. With just the two of them there, Wasp then carried Ant-Man to the core's center, and they both fired multiple [[Pym Particle Discs|Shrink Discs]] at it, which successfully returned the core to its regular size.
[[File:Wasp and Ant-Man face off with Kang.png|{{AltFloat}}|Wasp and [[Ant-Man]] are confronted by [[Kang]]]]
Wasp and Ant-Man fell to the ground, and when they got up, Wasp told Ant-Man that they had to get the core out of there, but Ant-Man stopped her, revealing that [[Kang the Conqueror]] had [[Cassie Lang]]. Janet joined them, and insisted that they leave, assuring Ant-Man that they would rescue Cassie. Kang then arrived, calling Wasp "Jellybean," and demanded the core be handed over. When they refused, he used his powers to take it, so Wasp and Ant-Man went to attack him, but he flicked them away with ease, knocking them out.{{Ref|AMatWQ}}

====[[Uprising in Axia]]====
[[File:Wasp and Ant-Man found by the Ants.png|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne and [[Scott Lang]] learn of the [[Ants]]]]
{{Quote|[[Kang the Conqueror|He]]'s getting out."<br>"Oh, no he's not.|Wasp and [[Giant-Man]]|Ant-Man and the Wasp: Quantumania}}
They woke up and were found by [[Hank Pym]], along with giant [[Ants]] that had advanced themselves during their time in the [[Quantum Realm]]. The three were determined to rescue [[Cassie Lang]] and [[Janet van Dyne]] from [[Kang the Conqueror]], and they were supplied with a strategy from the ants.
[[File:Wasp, Ant-Man and Hank Pym.png|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne witnesses [[Cassie Lang]]'s message]]
Returning to the [[Krylar's Yacht|ship]], they watched Kang's message be interrupted by Cassie, who gave a speech to motivate the citizens of [[Axia]] to fight back against Kang. Van Dyne was able to track the signal from Cassie's message, so they rushed to rescue her and Janet. They arrived at Axia, so Wasp and Ant-Man flew out of the ship, and they made their approach to the city, with Ant-Man turning into Giant-Man and Wasp standing on his shoulder. Giant-Man called out Kang, and when a fleet of ships began attacking, Wasp went to fight them, but there were too many.
[[File:The Wasp in flight.png|{{AltFloat}}|Wasp taking on [[Kang the Conqueror]]'s fleet]]
Fortunately, Cassie's speech worked and the [[Freedom Fighters]] came to their rescue. Wasp continued to destroy many of Kang's ships, swiftly flying through a few in a row and using her [[Wasp's Stingers|Stingers]] to explode the others. Wasp regrouped with Giant-Man and witnessed Kang begin he escape from the Quantum Realm, so he went to destroy the shields but failed. So, he came up with a plan for Wasp to throw him at the shields when shrunken down and then turn back into Giant-Man before impact, which worked.
[[File:Ant-Man, Wasp and Stature.png|{{AltFloat}}|Wasp, [[Ant-Man]] and [[Cassie Lang]] confront [[Kang]]]]
Wasp and Ant-Man reunited with Cassie, and when Kang joined the fight, the three rushed towards him and prepared to face off. Wasp and Ant-Man charged at the Conqueror, with Wasp distracting him with her Stingers so that Ant-Man could attack him, and then fighting him simultaneously while using their shrinking abilities to overwhelm him. Cassie joined the fight, but was quickly knocked away, followed by Wasp, who was swatted out of the air, and then Ant-Man who managed to land a few hard hits as Giant-Man.
[[File:Wasp meets MODOK.png|{{AltFloat}}|Wasp is awkwardly reunited with [[M.O.D.O.K.]]]]
The three collected themselves as Kang taunted them for being no match to his superior might, stating that their only value was talking to ants. At that moment, an army of ants arrived and swarmed all of Kang's forces. Pym arrived on the bridge, and was soon followed by the ants, who went to attack Kang. They were unable to get through his forcefield until it was destroyed by [[M.O.D.O.K.]], allowing the ants to defeat Kang. With Kang gone, they went to a dying M.O.D.O.K.'s side, and Wasp was confused when she realized he was Darren Cross.{{Ref|AMatWQ}}

====Defeating the Conqueror====
[[File:Janet, Cassie & Hope.png|{{AltFloat}}|Wasp makes it out of the [[Quantum Realm]]]]
{{Quote|You came back. I love you, Hope."<br>"I love you, Scott.|[[Ant-Man]] and Wasp|Ant-Man and the Wasp: Quantumania}}
[[Janet van Dyne]] made contact with the group, informing them that she was in the tower and that she could get them back home, but time was running out. They flew up to the top of the tower, where Janet had opened the portal out of the [[Quantum Realm]]. Once Janet and [[Hank Pym]] went through, Wasp followed and then [[Cassie Lang]], but [[Ant-Man]] didn't return, making them wonder what happened to him.
[[File:The Wasp (QM).png|{{AltFloat}}|Wasp stops [[Kang the Conqueror]]'s escape]]
After a short period of time, Wasp figured that Ant-Man was in trouble, so she went back through the portal, where she found [[Kang the Conqueror]] running towards it, so she blasted him with her [[Wasp's Stingers|Stingers]], knocking him away from the portal. When Kang got back up and headed back to the portal, Wasp proceeded to hit him with her blasts, causing him to crash into the [[Multiversal Engine Core]]. Ant-Man gave him one final hit, which broke the core, and it consumed Kang, resulting in it exploding, ultimately defeating the Conqueror.
[[File:Quantumania New Trailer (29).png|{{AltFloat}}|Wasp and [[Ant-Man]] embracing each other]]
The explosion destroyed the core and closed the portal, trapping Wasp and Ant-Man in the Quantum Realm. Ant-Man began to panic about Cassie's safety, but Wasp told him she was back home. They then hugged, which caused Ant-Man some pain, so Wasp went to let go of him, but he didn't want her to. Touched by her coming back and saving him, Ant-Man told Wasp he loved her, and she reciprocated, as they rested their heads on one another. They then looked out to the liberated [[Axia|city]], as the portal reopened behind them, and they went through it.{{Ref|AMatWQ}}

====Back to Normal====
[[File:Ant Family Dinner.png|{{AltFloat}}|Van Dyne having dinner with her family]]
{{Quote|This is good. We're all together.|[[Scott Lang]]|Ant-Man and the Wasp: Quantumania}}
Now that their family was reunited and the threat of [[Kang the Conqueror]] dealt with, everyone returned to their normal lives, with van Dyne dyeing her hair blonde. Because they all missed a few years of [[Cassie Lang]] growing up due to the [[Snap]], [[Scott Lang]] decided to hold a fake birthday party for her at a restaurant with van Dyne and her [[Hank Pym|par]][[Janet van Dyne|ents]].{{Ref|AMatWQ}}

==Powers and Abilities==
===Powers===
<!-- The power list and levels has been carefully reviewed and approved with the media released as of Avengers: Endgame. DO NOT MAKE arbitrary changes to them or it may lead to blocks. If something is wrong, please contact WikiProjects: Powers & Abilities -->
{{Quote|You go low, I go high."<br>"I have wings; why would I go low?|[[Ant-Man]] and Wasp|Ant-Man and the Wasp}}
*'''[[Wasp Suit]] Capabilities''': van Dyne had been gifted the [[Wasp Suit]] by her father, [[Hank Pym]], who had finally decided to tell her the truth about her mother and former Wasp, [[Janet van Dyne]]. Wasp then worked together with Pym to create weapons and an upgraded suit fit to her liking.
**'''Size Manipulation''': [[File:Ant-Man and the Wasp 101.jpg|thumb|250px|Wasp increasing in size to attack a goon]] Similar to the [[Ant-Man]]'s suit, van Dyne is able to reduce herself to the size of an insect by using Pym Particles in the belt of the suit to distance her atoms, effectively compacting her physical structure and allowing her to shrink down whenever necessary. She still maintains her regular sized strength and durability while in a reduced scale as the process amplifies the amount of force she can generate and increases her density. Additionally, the process of altering size compresses force and energy, manifesting as brief shockwaves of vibration around the target, which briefly augments her force and momentum as she returns to normal size. 
***'''Superhuman Strength''': When decreased in size, van Dyne possesses a certain degree of superhuman strength, able to easily overpower enemies when shrunken down. The momentum of her attacks also appears to be increased. As she shrinks and regrows in an instant, the power behind her attacks, combined with her already superhuman strength and combat skills, allow for her to defeat the most skilled of combatants within a fraction of a second.
***'''Superhuman Durability''': When decreased in size, van Dyne's body is hyper-compressed, and is much resistant to injury, enough to survive falls from great heights and other impacts that would injure or kill even normal sized humans. She was notably capable of taking blows from the extremely dangerous [[Ghost]].
**'''Superhuman Speed''': While wearing her suit, van Dyne can fly 125 miles per hour.<ref name="Facebook"/>
**'''Enhanced Reflexes''': The suit improves van Dyne's reflexes to avoid faster attacks.<ref name=Facebook>[https://www.facebook.com/antman/videos/459285234499094/ Ant-Man on Facebook]</ref>
**'''Flight''': [[File:Ant-Man and the Wasp 79.jpg|thumb|250px|Wasp flying in the air]] By utilizing four artificial insect-like wings, van Dyne can fly at impressive speeds and maneuver with great agility with ease, as evidenced when a knife was thrown at her while she was shrunken down. She was able to fly from the center of San Francisco to Fisherman's Wharf in a matter of minutes. She can also use the wings at full-size as blunt-force weapons.
**'''Energy Blast''': van Dyne can fire bolts of energy from the wrists of her [[Wasp's Stingers|gauntlets]]. They are powerful enough to blast burning holes in reinforced materials, incapacitate the [[Ghost]] mid-phase, and knock a man unconscious. Her gauntlets were later upgraded before the [[Snap]], now able to fire constant streams of concussive energy, powerful enough to push back the likes of [[Thanos/Cosmic Time Heist|Thanos]] during the [[Battle of Earth]] alongside [[Shuri]] and [[Pepper Potts]].  
**'''Insect Manipulation''': Through the use of the [[EMP Communication Device]] given to her by her father, van Dyne can use electromagnetic waves to communicate and control insects, primarily ants. The device uses electromagnetic waves to mimic pheromones and stimulate the olfactory nerve center of insect-sized organisms.

===Abilities===
<!-- The power list and levels has been carefully reviewed and approved with the media released as of Avengers: Endgame. DO NOT MAKE arbitrary changes to them or it may lead to blocks. If something is wrong, please contact WikiProjects: Powers & Abilities -->
{{Quote|It wasn't a message you put in [[Ant-Man|Scott]]'s head. It was an antenna."<br>"Clever girl. I'm so proud of you.|[[Hope van Dyne]] and Janet van Dyne|Ant-Man and the Wasp}}
*'''Genius-Level Intellect''': [[File:Ant-Man and the Wasp 138.jpg|thumb|250px|van Dyne working on the [[Quantum Tunnel]]]] Raised by [[Hank Pym]], van Dyne is an expert in many fields of science. Hope seemingly carries her own father's passions in chemistry and physics, which explains why she seemed confident in her understanding of the Ant-Man Suit to the point that she thought she could wear it to take down [[Darren Cross]].
{{Quote|So, while you were relaxing at home... we were building [[Quantum Tunnel|this]]. It's a tunnel. To the quantum realm.|Hope van Dyne to [[Scott Lang]]|Ant-Man and the Wasp}}
*'''Master Scientist''': Van Dyne is a highly skilled scientist, specializing in physics and chemistry.
*'''Master Engineer''': Van Dyne is a highly skilled engineer, being able to use her skill to build the [[Quantum Tunnel]] alongside his father.
*'''Master Businessperson''': Van Dyne's business acumen has risen to the point she was able to secure for herself a stable position in Pym Technologies' board. She possessed enough power in the company to have the deciding vote to remove [[Hank Pym]], the company's founder and CEO, from the company.
{{Quote|Hope trained in martial arts at a difficult time.|Hank Pym to [[Scott Lang]]|Ant-Man (film)}}
*'''Master Martial Artist''': [[File:GhostPinningDownWaspByAWall.jpg|thumb|250px|Wasp fighting against [[Ghost]]]] Van Dyne has trained in martial arts since she was a child, training [[Scott Lang]] in combat skills and fighting techniques, enabling him to become Ant-Man. Her martial arts prowess came in handy when she finally took the mantle of the Wasp. Van Dyne employs a mixed martial art including elements of {{WPS|muay Thai}}, {{WPS|Brazilian jiu-jitsu}}, {{WPS|Judo}}, {{WPS|kickboxing}}, and {{WPS|aikido}}.
*'''Expert Marksman''': ''To be added''
*'''Master Acrobat''': Van Dyne incorporates gymnastics and acrobatics into her fighting style as she battles opponents, notably dodging a knife thrown at her while shrunken, then using it as a platform to continue her assault.

